gomodel:SYNGO_5193  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: SNX27 co-localized with recycling endosome markers transferrin receptor and Rab11 in cultured hippocampal neurons (16 div) (Fig. 4b). Time-lapse imaging showed the mobilization of SNX27 along with recycling endosomes into spines (Fig. 4d,e, S4).\n\nSuppl. fig. 2 shows colocalization of epitopes for anti-SNX27 antibody with GFP-SNX27 and mCherry-SNX27 fluorescence.. Experimental description: \"Hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from P0 mouse pups\", p. 11\n\nGFP-SNX27 and mCherry SNX27 were generated by subcloning human SNX27 (Origene) into pEGFP-N1 or pmCherry-N1 (Clontech) using Bgl11 and BamH1.\n\nThe source or generation of the antibody for targeting endogenous SNX27 is not described." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5193" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

